We used this infrastructure in two ways.
First, we have a set of examples with known results, against which we can test a
potential rule set.
% We cannot prove formally that the rules evaluates all the programs we
% expect, since we have no specification of what we expect.
Second, before beginning a proof of confluence, we used QuickCheck \cite{quickcheck}
to generate test cases, and check them for confluence.
QuickCheck turned out to be invaluable at finding counterexamples to
